description:
When the plans for the future change, new bonds are created between Danilo, Lucas and Marcos. in between video-games and milk cups, pain and disappointment, they need to learn how to live together.

You, Me, and Him" (June 8 at 3:30 p.m.) from Brazil conveys the palpable struggle of Danilo (Daniel Tavares) a gay man forced to care for his younger brother Lucas (Eduardo Melo) after their parents are killed in an accident. As Danilo&#039;s lover, Marcos (Diego Torraca), adjusts to this new arrangement, the dynamics shift dramatically among these three men. Things change forever in multiple - and heart-wrenching - ways.
